refactor: replace assert2::assert! runtime checks with typed Result

All public API functions now return crate::Result (= Result<T, error::Error>),
removing panic-on-misuse from the library surface. assert2 moves to
dev-dependencies; only #[cfg(test)] blocks retain it.

Migrated functions:
- utils: prompt_password (Error::EmptyPassword), atomic_write
  (Error::AtomicPersist), is_file_encrypted
- config: add_one_path_to_crypt_list (Error::PathNotExist /
  PathNotRelative; now returns Result), add_paths_to_crypt_list
  (Error::Config)
- repo: Repo::open (Error::RepoNotFound / NotADirectory / Config),
  get_key (returns Result instead of panicking via .expect),
  check (Error::NoFile / FilesNotEncrypted), install_hook
  (Error::HookExists), GitCommand impls (Error::Git)
- crypt: encrypt_repo / decrypt_repo (Error::EmptyKey / NoFile /
  Argon2 / EncryptFailed / DecryptFailed / TruncatedChunk /
  FileTruncated), FileHeader::from_bytes (Error::InvalidMagic /
  UnsupportedVersion / UnsupportedAlgo)

anyhow::Context is retained for ergonomic context chaining; conversions
to crate::Error flow through Error::Other (#[from] anyhow::Error) and
Error::Io (#[from] std::io::Error).

Tests updated to match new lowercase error strings.
